      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Our feature of the night and we're leaning to POP AWARD (3) who resumes. She typically goes very well fresh, close up in the G3 How Now first up last time in. Her best form reads nicely for this and Stackhouse can get her into a good spot just behind the speed. GIVE ME SPACE (4) resumes, now with the Hayes yard. One run last time in at Eagle Farm was at Listed level and he was sent around at $2.50 having run second in a Magic Millions 3yo Guineas prior to that. Off a long break here but he's absolutely good enough. SOFT LOVE (6) resumes. She was excellent first up last time in at Caulfield and will be charging at them late from back in the field. CORNICHE (2) resumes for a new yard. He's contested much stronger races than this in the past, how well he's going for the stable is the query. A LITTLE DEEP (1) is going okay. This suits, just want to see her put a field away.",
